label: Pubic symphysis morphological stage
definition: A categorical measurement datum that describes age-related morphological changes to the pubic symphysis by comparing a specimen to a number of defined phases.

label: Female pubic symphysis morphological stage
definition: A categorical measurement datum that describes age-related morphological changes to the pubic symphysis in female individuals by comparing a specimen to the six phases defined by Brooks & Suchey (1990).
definition source: Brooks, S., & Suchey, J. M. (1990). Skeletal age determination based on the os pubis: a comparison of the Acsádi- Nemeskéri and Suchey-Brooks methods. Human Evolution 5(3), 227-238 . doi:10.1007/BF02437238

label: Male pubic symphysis morphological stage
definition: A categorical measurement datum that describes age-related morphological changes to the pubic symphysis in male individuals by comparing a specimen to the six phases defined by Brooks & Suchey (1990).
definition source: Brooks, S., & Suchey, J. M. (1990). Skeletal age determination based on the os pubis: a comparison of the Acsádi- Nemeskéri and Suchey-Brooks methods. Human Evolution 5(3), 227-238 . doi:10.1007/BF02437238

label: 95% age range
definition: A data item that describes an age range comprising 95% of all age-at-death estimates drawn by some method from a sample of individuals.

label: 95% age range for females
definition: A data item that specifies the 95% age range given by Brooks & Suchey (1990, Table 1) that corresponds to the morhplogical pubic symphysis phase displayed by one female specimen.
definition source: Brooks, S., & Suchey, J. M. (1990). Skeletal age determination based on the os pubis: a comparison of the Acsádi- Nemeskéri and Suchey-Brooks methods. Human Evolution 5(3), 227-238 . doi:10.1007/BF02437238

label: 95% age range for males
definition: A data item that specifies the 95% age range given by Brooks & Suchey (1990, Table 1) that corresponds to the morhplogical pubic symphysis phase displayed by one male specimen.
definition source: Brooks, S., & Suchey, J. M. (1990). Skeletal age determination based on the os pubis: a comparison of the Acsádi- Nemeskéri and Suchey-Brooks methods. Human Evolution 5(3), 227-238 . doi:10.1007/BF02437238

label: Determined age at death
definition: A conclusion based on data that integrates the data established in an age-at-death investigation evaluating degradation of the pubic symphysis into a conclusion concerning the individual's age at death.
